title: Mutiny on the Bounty
description: A tyrannical ship captain drives his crew to mutiny during a voyage to Tahiti.

title: A Night at the Opera
description: A sly business manager and two wacky friends help two opera singers achieve success while humiliating their stuffy and snobbish enemies.

title: The 39 Steps
description: A man in London tries to help a counter-espionage agent. But when the agent is killed and the man stands accused, he must go on the run to save himself and stop a spy ring.

title: Bride of Frankenstein
description: Mary Shelley reveals the main characters of her novel survived: Dr. Frankenstein, goaded by an even madder scientist, builds his monster a mate.

title: Top Hat
description: An American dancer comes to Britain and falls for a model whom he initially annoyed, but she mistakes him for his goofy producer.

title: Captain Blood
description: A doctor wrongly sentenced to slavery in the Caribbean escapes to become a pirate captain.

title: The Informer
description: In 1922 Dublin, a dim-witted man informs on his IRA friend for a 20-pound reward, leading to tragedy.

title: Dangerous
description: An alcoholic, self-destructive actress is rehabilitated by a sound architect who falls in love with her.

title: Alice Adams
description: A small-town girl with social ambitions tries to hide her humble background to impress a wealthy young man.

title: Anna Karenina
description: The wife of a Russian imperial minister leaves her husband and son for the love of a cavalry officer.

title: A Tale of Two Cities
description: In the French Revolution, a disillusioned English lawyer sacrifices his life to save the husband of the woman he loves.

title: The Lives of a Bengal Lancer
description: A British major and his two new officers battle rebellious tribesmen on the Northwest Frontier of India.

title: Naughty Marietta
description: A French princess flees an arranged marriage by traveling to New Orleans, where she falls in love with an Indian scout.

title: Gold Diggers of 1935
description: A group of guests at a luxury hotel are swindled and entertained by various performers, culminating in the famous 'Lullaby of Broadway' number.

title: Les Misérables
description: Jean Valjean, a man imprisoned for stealing bread, is pursued by the ruthless policeman Javert for decades.

title: The Dark Angel
description: A soldier blinded in WWI allows his family and fiancée to believe he is dead to spare them the burden of caring for him.

title: Becky Sharp
description: A social climbing English girl attempts to charm and marry her way into high society during the Napoleonic Wars.

title: China Seas
description: A captain must deal with pirates, a typhoon, and a romantic triangle aboard a ship bound for Singapore.

title: Magnificent Obsession
description: A reckless playboy inadvertently causes the blindness of a doctor's widow, then studies to become a surgeon to restore her sight.

title: The Little Colonel
description: A young girl brings her estranged grandfather and parents back together in the post-Civil War South.

title: Ruggles of Red Gap
description: An English butler is won in a poker game by a rough-and-tumble American from Red Gap, Washington, where he becomes a local celebrity.

title: Peter Ibbetson
description: Childhood sweethearts are separated but find each other years later, only to be separated again by a murder conviction, communicating through dreams.

title: Broadway Melody of 1936
description: A newspaper columnist tries to use a young dancer to frame a producer, but she ends up becoming a Broadway star.

title: David Copperfield
description: A gentle orphan discovers life and love in an indifferent adult world.

title: The Raven
description: A brilliant surgeon obsessed with Edgar Allan Poe saves a dancer's life and goes mad when he can't have her, using an escaped murderer to help him execute his torture devices.

title: Werewolf of London
description: A botanist seeking a rare flower in Tibet is bitten by a werewolf and brings the curse back to London.

title: Mark of the Vampire
description: A nobleman is found murdered, drained of blood, leading to suspicion of a vampire count residing in a nearby castle.

title: Mad Love
description: An insane surgeon replaces the crushed hands of a pianist with the hands of a knife-throwing murderer.

title: The Devil Is a Woman
description: A young Spanish revolutionary falls for a cold-hearted woman who destroys men for sport.

title: Annie Oakley
description: The story of sharpshooter Annie Oakley and her rise to fame in Buffalo Bill's Wild West Show.

title: G Men
description: A young lawyer joins the FBI to avenge the murder of his unarmed friend by a mobster.

title: Barbary Coast
description: A young woman arrives in San Francisco during the Gold Rush to marry her fiancé, only to find he has been killed.

title: Black Fury
description: A naive coal miner is manipulated into leading a strike, which results in violence and tragedy.

title: The Whole Town's Talking
description: A meek clerk who resembles a notorious gangster is given a special pass by the police to avoid arrest, which the gangster exploits.

title: Steamboat Round the Bend
description: A steamboat captain tries to prove his nephew's innocence in a murder trial while racing a rival steamboat.

title: The Good Fairy
description: A naive orphanage usherette tries to bring good luck to everyone she meets in Budapest, creating chaos along the way.

title: Hands Across the Table
description: A manicurist looking for a rich husband falls for a playboy who is actually broke.

title: Sylvia Scarlett
description: A young woman disguises herself as a boy to escape France with her embezzling father, leading to romantic complications.

title: The Call of the Wild
description: A prospector sets out across the Yukon with a wild dog that he rescues and befriends.

title: A Midsummer Night's Dream
description: Shakespeare's fantasy comedy about mismatched lovers and mischievous fairies in an enchanted forest.

title: Roberta
description: An American football player inherits a Parisian fashion house and falls in love with the head designer.

title: In Old Kentucky
description: A rivalry between two families of horse trainers is complicated by romance and a big race.

title: The Littlest Rebel
description: A young girl in the Civil War South befriends a Union officer to help her Confederate father.

title: Show Them No Mercy!
description: A young couple is held hostage by a gang of kidnappers demanding a ransom.

title: The Glass Key
description: A political boss is accused of murder, and his loyal right-hand man tries to clear his name.

title: Murder in the Fleet
description: A naval officer tries to solve a murder mystery aboard his ship before it sets sail.

title: Curly Top
description: A wealthy bachelor adopts an orphan and her older sister, leading to romance and songs.

title: Mississippi
description: A pacifist refuses to duel for his fiancé's honor, gets kicked out, and joins a riverboat troupe where he becomes a singing star.

title: Rumba
description: A wealthy heiress falls for a dancer in Havana, complicating her life and his career.

title: The Scoundrel
description: A cynical publisher dies in a plane crash and returns as a ghost to find one person who will weep for him.
